Source: occase
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Marcelo Zimbres <mzimbres@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>=11~)
Standards-Version: 4.1.4
Homepage: http://www.occase.de

Package: occase-db
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Replaces:
 occase-db (<< 1.0.0-1),
Description: Realtime database for the occase app (server).
 A sigle threaded database that uses websocket and scales per process.
 .
 This package contains only the database.

Package: occase-mms
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Replaces:
 occase-mms (<< 1.0.0-1),
Description: Multimedia server used by the occase app (server).
 A very simple single threaded Http server used to post and get
 multimedia data.
 .
 This package contains only the server.

Package: occase-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Replaces:
 occase-tools (<< 1.0.0-1),
Description: Tools to configure and monitor the occase servers.
 Contains the tools to configure and monitor the occase server.
 For example load redis with the channels, display current number of
 websocket sessions etc.
 .
 This package contains the occase tools.

Package: occase-notify
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Replaces:
 occase-notify (<< 1.0.0-1),
Description: Push notification server used by the occase app.
 A single threaded server that notifes users that send push notifcations to
 users that are not online.
 .
 This package contains only the notify server.
